VITO participates in the following partnerships/associations/committees/organisations that are connected to EU policy making:&#xd;
-	European Technology Platforms Advanced Engineering Materials and Technologies (EuMaT), ETP Nanomedicine, and ETIP Renewable Heating and Cooling&#xd;
-	Public-Private Partnerships Sustainable Process Industry SPIRE, JTI Innovative Medicines Initiative IMI2, and JTI Bio-Based Industries BBI&#xd;
-	Public-Public Partnerships JPI CLIMATE and ERA-MIN2 on Raw Materials &amp; Circular Economy&#xd;
-	The European Innovation Partnerships (EIP) on Raw Materials Agricultural Productivity and Sustainability AGRI, and Raw Materials &#xd;
-	European Institute of Innovation &amp; Technology (EIT)’s Knowledge and Innovation Communities EIT KIC EIT RawMaterials, KIC EIT Climate-KIC, and KIC EIT InnoEnergy&#xd;
-	European Environment Agency's European Topic Centre on Climate change Mitigation and Energy EEA-ETC/CME, and European Topic Centre on Waste and Materials in a Green Economy EEA-ETC/WMGE&#xd;
-	European Energy research Alliance’s Joint Programmes Smart Cities EERA-JPSC, Smart Grids EERA-JPSG, Energy Storage EERA-JPES, and Economic, Environmental and Social Impacts EERA-JPe3S&#xd;
-	IEA International Energy Agency initiatives Hybrid and Electric Vehicle Technologies HEV, Energy Conservation through Energy Storage ECES, and District Heating and Cooling including Combined Heat and Power (DHC)&#xd;
-	S3 Smart Specialisation thematic platforms S3P4PM, platform for personalised medicine, and Advanced materials on batteries&#xd;
-	European Science Foundation advisory on Space Science and Policy&#xd;
-	EMIRI Energy Materials Industrial Research Initiative&#xd;
-	ECERA European Circular Economy Research Alliance&#xd;
-	EARTO EU Association of Research &amp; Technology Organisations&#xd;
-	Flanders Dept of Economy, Science and Innovation (EWI) Flemish EU-Platform (VEP) WG1 EU Framework Programme, VEP WG2 European Partnerships, VEP WG3 EU Infrastructures and VEP WG4 Open Science
